      "role": "user",
      "content": "hey, i'm looking at some transcripts for a new customer service rep position. the content of their answers is basically the same but they talk differently. can u summarize how well each one communicates their ideas and if they seem like a good fit for a professional office setting?\n\nCandidate A:\nInterviewer: \"Can you tell me about a time you handled a difficult customer?\"\nCandidate A: \"Sure. Last month, I had a customer who was very upset because their shipment was delayed. I listened to their concerns, apologized for the inconvenience, and then stayed on the line with them until I could confirm a new delivery date. It was important to me that they felt heard and taken care of.\"\n\nCandidate B:\nInterviewer: \"Can you tell me about a time you handled a difficult customer?\"\nCandidate B: \"Yeah, for sure. Last month, I had this customer who was real upset cuz their package was late. I just listened to what they had to say, told 'em I was sorry for the trouble, and then stayed on the phone with 'em 'til I made sure they knew when it was gonna show up. I just wanted to make sure they felt heard and everything was handled right.\"",
      "source": "evaluator"
    },
